      <h3>Why degree abbreviations matter</h3>
      <p>
        Degree abbreviations help students, employers, and schools quickly identify educational level
        and discipline. They are especially useful in resumes, faculty bios, admissions pages, and
        academic directories. Because some abbreviations vary by institution, it is a good idea to
        use the style preferred by the school or publisher.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="nursing-acronyms">
      <h2>Nursing acronyms</h2>
      <p>
        Nursing acronyms are widely searched because many students compare entry points, licensure
        pathways, and advanced practice options. These terms are important because they separate
        educational degrees from professional credentials and job roles.
      </p>

      <div class="data-table">
        <table>
